-- Canadian Bankruptcies Fall 1.3% in April From March, Decline 21% on Year
-- Alexandre Deslongchamps
-- 2010-07-14T17:20:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/canadian-bankruptcies-decline-1-3-in-april-from-march-fall-21-on-year.html

          
          
             Canadian bankruptcies fell 1.3
percent in April from the previous month, the countryâ€™s
bankruptcy superintendent  reported  on its website.  
 The number of bankruptcies filed by consumers and
businesses declined to 9,068 in April. From a year ago, they
fell 21 percent.  
 Adjusting for seasonality, bankruptcies rose 4.1 percent on
the month in April, according to calculations by Scotia Capital
sent by economist  Derek Holt  in an e-mail.  
 The annual bankruptcy rate for consumers rose to 4.5 per
thousand in 2009, from 3.4 in 2008, the superintendent also
 reported . For businesses, the rate fell to 2.4 per thousand in
2009, from 2.6 in 2008.  
